{"title_page": "Beach Bunny (band)", "text_new": "{{Infobox musical artist\n| name            = Beach Bunny <3\n| image           =\n| image_size      = \n| image_upright   = \n| landscape       = <!-- yes, if wide image, otherwise leave blank -->\n| alt             = \n| caption         = \n| background      = group_or_band\n| alias           = \n| origin          = Chicago, Illinois\n| genre           = [[Indie pop]], [[surf pop]], [[bedroom pop]] [[indie rock]]\n| years_active    = {{start date|2015}}\u2013present\n| label           = \n| associated_acts = \n| website         = <!-- {{URL|www.example.com}} or {{Official URL}} -->\n| current_members = *Lili Trifilio\n*Matt Henkels \n*Jon Alvarado\n*Anthony Vaccaro\n| past_members    = *Aidan Cada\n| module          = \n| module2         = \n| module3         = \n}}\n\n'''Beach Bunny''' is an American [[indie pop]] band from [[Chicago]], [[Illinois]].\n\n==History==\nBeach Bunny began in 2015 when Lili Trifilio recorded a song titled \"6 Weeks\". The next year, Trifilio released her first EP titled ''Animalism''.<ref name=\"chicagotribune\">{{cite web |last1=Stewart |first1=Allison |title=Chicago's Beach Bunny is about to face being grown up and becoming the next big thing at the same time |url=https://www.chicagotribune.com/entertainment/music/ct-ott-beach-bunny-0104-story.html |publisher=[[Chicago Tribune]] |accessdate=31 January 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"chicagoreader\">{{cite web |last1=De La Cerda |first1=Marissa |title=Beach Bunny\u2019s indie pop goes from dorms to DIY shows to Thalia Hall |url=https://www.chicagoreader.com/Bleader/archives/2018/10/31/beach-bunnys-indie-pop-goes-from-dorms-to-diy-shows-to-thalia-hall |publisher=[[Chicago Reader]] |accessdate=31 January 2019}}</ref> Also in 2016, Beach Bunny released an EP titled ''Pool Party''.<ref name=\"hooliganmagazine1\">{{cite web |last1=Gates |first1=Meggie |title=Beach Bunny and the Passage of Time |url=http://www.hooliganmagazine.com/blog/2018/8/30/beach-bunny-and-the-passage-of-time |publisher=Hooligan Magazine |accessdate=1 February 2019}}</ref> In 2017, Beach Bunny released another EP titled ''Crybaby''.<ref name=\"chicagoreader1\">{{cite web |last1=Galil |first1=Leor |title=Chicago power-pop band Beach Bunny show why they're one of the best in town with Prom Queen |url=https://www.chicagoreader.com/chicago/chicago-power-pop-band-beach-bunny-show-why-theyre-one-of-the-best-in-town-with-prom-queen/Content?oid=65987181 |accessdate=1 February 2019}}</ref> In 2018, Beach Bunny released their fourth EP titled ''Prom Queen''.<ref name=\"chicagoreader1\"/><ref name=\"pastemagazine\">{{cite web |last1=Kamp |first1=Justin |title=Daily Dose: Beach Bunny, \"Prom Queen\" |url=https://www.pastemagazine.com/articles/2019/01/daily-dose-beach-bunny-prom-queen.html |publisher=[[Paste (magazine)|Paste]] |accessdate=1 February 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"fourteeneastmagazine\">{{cite web |last1=Happold |first1=Madeline |title=Beach Bunny Leans Into Growing Pains With \u201cProm Queen\u201d EP |url=http://fourteeneastmag.com/index.php/2018/08/10/beach-bunny-leans-into-growing-pains-with-prom-queen-ep/ |publisher=Fourteen East Magazine}}</ref><ref name=\"hooliganmagazine\">{{cite web |last1=Corrall |first1=Cody |title=PREMIERE: Beach Bunny\u2019s \u2018painkiller\u2019 Lets You Dance Away the Heartbreak |url=http://www.hooliganmagazine.com/music/2018/7/13/premiere-beach-bunnys-painkiller-lets-you-dance-away-the-heartbreak |publisher=Hooligan Magazine |accessdate=1 February 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn October 31, 2019, the band announced that they had signed to [[Mom + Pop Music]] and released their first full-length album, ''Honeymoon'', on February 14, 2020.<ref name=\"consequenceofsound\">{{cite web |last1=Kaye |first1=Ben |title=Beach Bunny announce debut LP Honeymoon, share Origins of \u201cDream Boy\u201d: Stream |url=https://consequenceofsound.net/2019/10/beach-bunny-dream-boy-origins-honeymoon-stream/ |publisher=[[Consequence of Sound]]