    = \n}}\n\n'''Toni Liias''' (born 16 October 1986) is a Finnish [[bicycle racing|racing cyclist]]. He won the [[Finnish National Road Race Championships|Finnish national road race title]] in 2009.<ref name=\"CyclingArchives\">{{cite web |url=http://www.cyclingarchives.com/coureurfiche.php?coureurid=55248 |title=Toni Liias |accessdate=5 May 2014 |work=Cycling Archives}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{cycling archives|55248}}\n\n{{Finnish National Road Race Championships (men) |state=collapsed}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Liias, Toni}}\n[[Category:1986 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Finnish male cyclists]]\n[[Category:Place of birth missing (living people)]]\n{{Finland-cycling-bio-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Lugnuts", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Toni_Liias"}
{"title_page": "Boban Marjanovi\u0107", "text_new": "{{short description|Serbian basketball player}}\n{{Infobox basketball biography\n| name = Boban Marjanovi\u0107 long pp\n| image = Boban Marjanovic 51 (cropped).jpg\n| image_size = 250px\n| caption = Marjanovi\u0107 with the [[Los Angeles Clippers]] in November 2018\n| position = [[Center (basketball)|Center]]\n| height_ft = 7\n| height_in = 4\n| weight_lb = 290\n| league = [[National Basketball Association|NBA]]\n| team = Dallas Mavericks\n| number = 51\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1988|8|15}}\n| birth_place = [[Boljevac]], [[Socialist Republic of Serbia|SR Serbia]], [[Socialist Federal Republic of Yugoslavia|SFR Yugoslavia]]\n| nationality = Serbian\n| draft_year = 2010\n| career_start = 2006\n| career_end =\n| years1 = 2006\u20132010\n| team1 = [[KK Hemofarm|Hemofarm]]\n| years2 = 2007\n| team2 = \u2192[[KK Swisslion Takovo|Swisslion Takovo]]\n| years3 = 2010\u20132011\n| team3 = [[PBC CSKA Moscow|CSKA Moscow]]\n| years4 = 2011\n| team4 = \u2192[[BC \u017dalgiris|\u017dalgiris]]\n| years5 = 2011\u20132012\n| team5 = [[BC Nizhny Novgorod|Nizhny Novgorod]]\n| years6 = 2012\n| team6 = \u2192[[KK Radni\u010dki Kragujevac|Radni\u010dki Kragujevac]]\n| years7 = 2012\u20132013\n| team7 = [[KK Mega Vizura|Mega Vizura]]\n| years8 = 2013\u20132015\n| team8 = [[KK Crvena zvezda|Crvena zvezda]]\n| years9 = {{nbay|2015|full=y}}\n| team9 = [[San Antonio Spurs]]\n| years10 = 2015\u20132016\n| team10 = \u2192[[Austin Spurs]]\n| years11 = {{nbay|2016|start}}\u2013{{nbay|2017|end}}\n| team11 = [[Detroit Pistons]]\n| years12 = {{nbay|2017|end}}\u2013{{nbay|2018|end}}\n| team12 = [[Los Angeles Clippers]]\n| years13 = {{nbay|2018|end}}\n| team13 = [[Philadelphia 76ers]]\n| years14 = {{nbay|2019|start}}\u2013present\n| team14 = [[Dallas Mavericks]]\n| highlights = \n* Nba Champion (2015-2019)\n* [[All-EuroLeague|All-EuroLeague First Team]] ([[2014\u201315 Euroleague|2015]])\n* 3\u00d7 [[BLS Super League MVP|Serbian Super League MVP]] ([[2012\u201313 Basketball League of Serbia|2013]]\u2013[[2014\u201315 Basketball League of Serbia|2015]])\n* [[Basketball League of Serbia|Serbian League]] champion ([[2014\u201315 Basketball League of Serbia|2015]])\n* [[ABA League]] champion ([[2014\u201315 ABA League|2015]])\n* [[ABA League Final Four MVP|ABA League playoffs MVP]] (2015)\n* 2\u00d7 [[All-ABA League Team]] ([[2013\u201314 ABA League#The ideal five and coach of the season|2014]], [[2014\u201315 ABA League#The ideal five and coach of the season|2015]])\n* 2\u00d7 [[Serbian Basketball Cup|Serbian Cup]] winner ([[2013\u201314 Radivoj Kora\u0107 Cup|2014]], [[Radivoj Kora\u0107 Cup 2014-15|2015]])\n* [[LKL All-Star Game|LKL All-Star]] ([[2011 LKL All-Star Game|2011]])\n* [[Lithuanian Basketball League|Lithuanian League]] champion ([[2010\u201311 LKL season|2011]])\n* [[Baltic Basketball League|Baltic League]] champion ([[2010\u201311 Baltic Basketball League|2011]])\n* [[LKF Cup|Lithuanian Cup]] winner (2011)\n| bbr = marjabo01\n| profile = boban_marjanovic\n| medaltemplates = \n{{MedalSport|Men's [[basketball]]}}\n{{MedalCountry|{{bk|SRB}}}}\n{{Medal|Competition|[[EuroBasket]]}}\n{{Medal|Silver|[[EuroBasket 2017|2017 Turkey]]|}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[FIBA Under-19 World Cup]]}}\n{{MedalGold|[[2007 FIBA Under-19 World Championship|2007 Serbia]]|[[Serbia men's national under-19 basketball team|Team]]}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[FIBA Europe Under-20 Championship]]}}\n{{MedalGold|[[2008 FIBA Europe Under-20 Championship|2008 Latvia]]|[[Serbia men's national under-20 basketball team|Team]]}}\n}}\n[[File:BobanMarjanovic.JPG|thumb|Marjanovi\u0107 playing with [[KK Crvena zvezda|Crvena zvezda]] during the 2014\u201315 season.]]\n\n'''Boban Marjanovi\u0107''' ({{lang-sr-cyr|\u0411\u043e\u0431\u0430\u043d \u041c\u0430\u0440\u0458\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438\u045b}}; born August 15, 1988) is a Serbian professional [[basketball]] player for the [[Dallas Mavericks]] of the [[National Basketball Association]] (NBA). He also represents the [[Serbia national basketball team|Serbian national basketball team]] in international competitions. Standing at 7-foot-4-inch playing the [[Center (basketball)|center]] position, he is the 2nd [[List of tallest players in National Basketball Association history|tallest active player in the NBA]], after rookie [[Tacko Fall]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.hispanosnba.com/players/nba-active/index|title=Active NBA players (2018-19 season)|last=Hispanosnba.com|website=hispanosnba.com|language=en|access-date=2019-05-10}}</ref> In [[2014\u201315 Euroleague|2015]], Marjanovi\u0107 earned an [[All-EuroLeague Team|All-EuroLeague First Team]] selection.\n\n==Professional career==\n===Early years===\nMarjanovi\u0107 began playing basketball with the youth teams of [[Boljevac]]-based club [[KK Rtanj|Rtanj]].<ref name=youthint>{{cite news|last1=Nikoli\u0107|first1=R.|title=Boban Marjanovi\u0107 i mit o pradedinom opanku|url=http://www.novosti.rs/vesti/sport.295.html:431901-Boban-Marjanovic-i-mit-o-pradedinom-opanku|accessdate=30 September 2015|work=novosti.rs|date=2 May 2013}}</ref> At the age of 14, he moved to Serbian professional team [[KK Hemofarm|Hemofarm]]. He was already {{height|m=2.09}} tall at the time.<ref name=youthint/>  He played in their youth categories until the 2005\u201306 season.\n\nMarjanovi\u0107 joined Hemofarm's first team, playing in the [[ABA League|Adriatic League]], in the second half of the 2005\u201306 season. He played there until January 2007 when he was [[loan (sports)|loaned]] to the [[Basketball League of Serbia|Serbian League]] team [[KK Swisslion Takovo|Swisslion Takovo]]. After half a season there, he returned to Hemofarm. In the following seasons, he played an important role for his team. His teammates included [[Stefan Markovi\u0107]] and [[Milan Ma\u010dvan]], with whom he had played on the Serbian junior national team.\n\n===2010\u20132012===\nIn the summer of 2010, Marjanovi\u0107 signed a three-year contract with [[PBC CSKA Moscow|CSKA Moscow]], on the insistence of [[Du\u0161ko Vujo\u0161evi\u0107]].<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.euroleague.net/news/i/73477/180 | title=CSKA Moscow adds size with Marjanovic | publisher=euroleague.net | date=July 6, 2010 | accessdate=February 22, 2013}}</ref> After Vujo\u0161evi\u0107 was fired, Marjanovi\u0107 lost his place in CSKA's first team. On December 31, 2010, he was [[loan (sports)|loaned]] to [[BC \u017dalgiris|\u017dalgiris]], until the end of the 2010\u201311 season.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.euroleague.net/euroleaguenews/transactions/2010-11-signings/i/80976/4465/zalgiris-gets-center-marjanovic-on-loan-from-cska |title=ZALGIRIS gets center Marjanovic on loan |publisher=euroleague.net |date=December 31, 2010 |accessdate=February 22, 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110615182745/http://www.euroleague.net/euroleaguenews/transactions/2010-11-signings/i/80976/4465/zalgiris-gets-center-marjanovic-on-loan-from-cska |archivedate=June 15, 2011 }}</ref>\n\nIn July 2011, he signed for [[BC Nizhny Novgorod|Nizhny Novgorod]],<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.sportando.com/en/europe/russia/87020/boban-marjanovic-moves-to-bc-nizhny-novgorod.html | title=Boban Marjanovic moves to BC Nizhny Novgorod | publisher=sportando.net | date=July 2, 2011 | accessdate=February 22, 2013}}</ref> staying there for half a season. In January 2012, he returned to Serbia and signed for [[KK Radni\u010dki Kragujevac|Radni\u010dki Kragujevac]] on loan for the rest of the 2011\u201312 season.<ref>{{cite news | url=https://sport.blic.rs/kosarka/domaca-kosarka-i-aba/boban-marjanovic-pojacao-radnicki-iz-kragujevca/tf6qq0g | title=Boban Marjanovi\u0107 poja\u010dao Radni\u010dki iz Kragujevca | language=Serbian | publisher=blic.rs | date=January 7, 2012 | accessdate=February 22, 2013}}</ref>\n\n===Mega Vizura===\nIn July 2012, he signed a contract with Serbian team [[KK Mega Vizura|Mega Vizura]] for the 2012\u201313 season.<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.sportando.com/en/europe/other-leagues/93726/boban-marjanovic-inks-with-mega-vizura.html | title=Boban Marjanovic inks with Mega Vizura | publisher=sportando.net | date=July 20, 2012 | accessdate=February 22, 2013}}</ref> He was named [[BLS Super League MVP|the MVP of the Serbian League]].<ref>{{cite news | url=http://sport.blic.rs/Kosarka/Domaca-kosarka-i-ABA/233826/Boban-Marjanovic-MVP-Superlige-Rakocevic-drugi-Bakic-treci | title=Boban Marjanovi\u0107 MVP Superlige, Rako\u010devi\u0107 drugi, Baki\u0107 tre\u0107i | language=Serbian | publisher=blic.rs | accessdate=July 2, 2013}}</ref>\n\n===Crvena Zvezda===\n====2013\u201314 season====\nOn July 2, 2013, Marjanovi\u0107 signed a two-year contract with [[KK Crvena Zvezda|Crvena zvezda]].<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.sportando.com/en/cups/adriatic-league/102882/red-star-adds-size-with-boban-marjanovic.html | title=Red Star adds size with Boban Marjanovic | publisher=Sportando.net | accessdate=July 2, 2013 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161220171439/http://www.sportando.com/en/cups/adriatic-league/102882/red-star-adds-size-with-boban-marjanovic.html | archive-date=December 20, 2016 | url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Marjanovi\u0107 dve godine u Zvezdi!|url=http://www.b92.net/sport/kosarka/vesti.php?yyyy=2013&mm=07&dd=02&nav_id=728527|work=b92.net|accessdate=2 July 2013|language=sr}}</ref> In December 2013, he was named [[EuroLeague MVP of the Round|EuroLeague MVP of the Round for Round 10]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Regular season Round 10 bwin MVP: Boban Marjanovic, Crvena Zvezda Telekom|url=http://www.euroleague.net/news/i/126938/180|accessdate=April 2, 2014|newspaper=Euroleague.net|date=December 21, 2013}}</ref> In April 2014, along with his teammate [[DeMarcus Nelson]], he was selected for [[ABA League Ideal Starting Five|the Ideal Team]] for the [[2013\u201314 ABA League]] season.<ref>{{cite web|title=The ideal five of the 2013/14 season selected |url=http://www.abaliga.com/a7487/News/The_ideal_five_of_the_2013/14_season_selected.html |work=abaliga.com |accessdate=21 April 2014 |url-status=bot: unknown |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20140421084230/http://www.abaliga.com/a7487/News/The_ideal_five_of_the_2013/14_season_selected.html |archivedate=21 April 2014 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=ABA: \u2019Ve\u010diti\u2019 i \u0160ari\u0107 u timu lige|url=http://www.b92.net/sport/kosarka/vesti.php?yyyy=2014&mm=04&dd=21&nav_id=838871|work=b92.net|accessdate=21 April 2014|language=sr}}</ref>\n\n====2014\u201315 season====\nIn the first game of the [[2014\u201315 Euroleague|2014\u201315]] EuroLeague season, Marjanovi\u0107 led his team to a 76\u201368 victory against [[Galatasaray S.K. (men's basketball)|Galatasaray]], scoring 22 points and pulling down 10 rebounds in 28 minutes on the court.<ref>{{cite news|title=Crvena Zvezda takes first Game of the Week against Galatasaray|url=http://www.euroleague.net/main/results/showgame?gamecode=10&pcode=LMG&seasoncode=E2014#!report|accessdate=18 October 2014|work=euroleague.net}}</ref> He was later named the EuroLeague MVP of the Round for Round 1.<ref>{{cite news|title=Regular season Round 1 bwin MVP: Boban Marjanovic, Crvena Zvezda Telekom Belgrade|url=http://www.euroleague.net/news/i/142316/180|accessdate=18 October 2014|work=euroleague.net}}</ref> On November 22, 2014, he recorded 23 points and a career-high 17 rebounds, for a [[Performance Index Rating|total index rating]] of 39 in a double overtime 103\u2013110 loss against Galatasaray.<ref>{{cite news|title=EL: Erceg ukrao pobedu Zvezdi!|url=http://www.b92.net/sport/kosarka/vesti.php?yyyy=2014&mm=11&dd=21&nav_id=926813|accessdate=21 November 2014|work=b92.net|language=Serbian}}</ref> At the time, his 17 rebounds in a single game was the highest number of rebounds by any player in the EuroLeague since 2011-12.<ref>{{cite news|title=Erceg, Arroyo star in Galatasaray\u2019s 2OT win over Crvena Zvezda|url=http://www.euroleague.net/main/results/showgame?gamecode=70&pcode=DHF&seasoncode=E2014#!report|accessdate=21 November 2014|work=euroleague.net}}</ref>\n\nOn April 9, in a game against [[Panathinaikos B.C.|Panathinaikos]], he set the [[EuroLeague records since the 2000\u201301 season|EuroLeague record since the 2000\u201301 season]] for the most rebounds in a single season with 256, passing the previous record of [[Mirsad T\u00fcrkcan]], who had 248 rebounds in the [[2002\u201303 Euroleague|2002\u201303]] season.<ref name=euromilestone>{{cite news|title=Zvezda's Marjanovic sets rebounds mark to end milestone season|url=http://www.euroleague.net/news/i/5vk5m9esb588vye5|accessdate=10 April 2015|work=euroleague.net|issue=9 April 2015}}</ref> He also set the EuroLeague record for the most [[Double (basketball)#double-double|double-double]]s in a season with 16, surpassing the record of 14 set by [[Tanoka Beard]] in the [[2004\u201305 Euroleague|2004\u201305]] season.<ref name=euromilestone/> Over 24 EuroLeague games, he averaged all career-highs of 16.6 points, a league-leading 10.7 rebounds and a record (since the EuroLeague 2000\u201301 season) of 25.67 in [[Performance Index Rating|PIR]].<ref name=euromilestone/><ref>{{cite news|title=Marjanovi\u0107 u istoriji Evrolige!|url=http://www.b92.net/sport/kosarka/vesti.php?yyyy=2015&mm=04&dd=09&nav_id=979123|accessdate=10 April 2015|work=b92.net|language=Serbian}}</ref>\n\nOn April 2, 2015, he was selected for [[ABA League Ideal Starting Five|the Ideal Team]] for the 2014\u201315 ABA League season.<ref>{{cite news|title=Marjanovi\u0107 heads the ideal five |url=http://www.abaliga.com/a9653/News/Marjanovic_heads_the_ideal_five.html |accessdate=9 May 2015 |work=abaliga.com |date=2 April 2015 |url-status=bot: unknown |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20150404172555/http://www.abaliga.com/a9653/News/Marjanovic_heads_the_ideal_five.html |archivedate=4 April 2015 }}</ref> Later that month, he helped his team to win the [[2014\u201315 ABA League]] trophy.<ref>{{cite news|title=Crvena zvezda is the new ABA League champion! |url=http://www.abaliga.com/a9839/News/_Crvena_zvezda_is_the_new_ABA_League_champion_.html |accessdate=6 May 2015 |work=abaliga.com |date=30 April 2015 |url-status=bot: unknown |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20150710215548/http://www.abaliga.com/a9839/News/_Crvena_zvezda_is_the_new_ABA_League_champion_.html |archivedate=10 July 2015 }}</ref> He was named the [[ABA League Final Four MVP|MVP of the ABA League playoffs]].<ref>{{cite news|title=The MVP is... Boban Marjanovi\u0107! |url=http://www.abaliga.com/a9840/News/The_MVP_is..._Boban_Marjanovic_.html |accessdate=6 May 2015 |work=abaliga.com |date=30 April 2015 |url-status=bot: unknown |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20150501093540/http://www.abaliga.com/a9840/News/The_MVP_is..._Boban_Marjanovic_.html |archivedate=1 May 2015 }}</ref> In May 2015, he was chosen for the [[All-EuroLeague Team|All-EuroLeague First Team]].<ref>{{cite news|title=All-Euroleague First and Second Teams announced|url=http://www.euroleague.net/news/i/5xtj7vjfuokfw7g8|accessdate=8 May 2015|work=euroleague.net}}</ref>\n\nOn June 5, 2015, Marjanovi\u0107 was named the [[BLS Super League MVP|Serbian Super League MVP]] for the third consecutive season, having helped his team to reach first place in the regular season with a record of 13\u20131.<ref>{{cite news|title=Bobi Marjanovi\u0107 \u2013 MVP, Nikola Joki\u0107 -najefikasniji|url=http://kls.rs/vest.php?id=1694|accessdate=5 June 2015|work=kls.rs|date=5 June 2015|language=Serbian}}</ref> Crvena zvezda won the [[2014\u201315 Basketball League of Serbia|2014\u201315 Serbian League]] championship after a 3\u20130 series victory over [[KK Partizan|Partizan Belgrade]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Be\u0107agovi\u0107|first1=M.|title=\"Delije\" do\u010dekale: Ko\u0161arka\u0161i Zvezde \u0161ampioni Srbije posle 17 godina!|url=http://sport.blic.rs/Kosarka/Domaca-kosarka-i-ABA/274309/Delije-docekale-Kosarkasi-Zvezde-sampioni-Srbije-posle-17-godina|accessdate=20 June 2015|work=sport.blic.rs|date=18 June 2015|language=Serbian}}</ref>\n\n===San Antonio Spurs (2015\u20132016)===\nOn July 17, 2015, Marjanovi\u0107 signed a one-year, $1.2 million contract with the [[San Antonio Spurs]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nba.com/spurs/spurs-sign-boban-marjanovic|title=Spurs Sign Boban Marjanovic|work=NBA.com|date=July 17, 2015|accessdate=July 17, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Spurs officially sign Boban Marjanovic|url=http://www.foxsports.com/nba/story/spurs-officially-sign-boban-marjanovic-072015|accessdate=30 September 2015|work=foxsports.com|date=20 July 2015}}</ref> He made his NBA debut on October 30, recording 6 points and 5 rebounds in the Spurs' 102\u201375 win over the [[Brooklyn Nets]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Leonard, Duncan lead Spurs to 102-75 win over Nets|url=http://www.nba.com/games/20151030/BKNSAS/gameinfo.html|accessdate=31 October 2015|work=NBA.com|date=31 October 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151126060803/http://www.nba.com/games/20151030/BKNSAS/gameinfo.html|archive-date=26 November 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref> On December 4, he was assigned to the [[Austin Spurs]], San Antonio's [[NBA Development League|D-League]] affiliate.<ref>{{cite news|title=SPURS ASSIGN BOBAN MARJANOVIC & RAY McCALLUM TO AUSTIN SPURS|url=http://www.nba.com/spurs/spurs-assign-boban-marjanovic-ray-mccallum-austin-spurs|accessdate=December 4, 2015|work=NBA.com|date=December 4, 2015}}</ref> He was recalled by San Antonio on December 6,<ref>{{cite news|title=Spurs Recall Boban Marjanovic from Austin Spurs|url=http://www.nba.com/spurs/spurs-recall-boban-marjanovic-austin-spurs|accessdate=December 6, 2015|work=NBA.com|date=December 6, 2015}}</ref> and, the following day, scored 18 points on 8-of-10 shooting in a 119\u201368 win over the [[Philadelphia 76ers]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Spurs rest starters, still romp 119-68 past hapless 76ers|url=http://www.nba.com/games/20151207/SASPHI/gameinfo.html|accessdate=December 7, 2015|work=NBA.com|date=December 7, 2015}}</ref> On December 28, in a win over the [[Minnesota Timberwolves]], Marjanovi\u0107 provided a spark off the bench with [[Tim Duncan]] out injured and [[LaMarcus Aldridge]] limited to six points. Marjanovi\u0107 scored 17 points on 7-of-7 shooting in just 14 minutes to help the Spurs defeat the Timberwolves 101\u201395 and extend their franchise-record home winning streak to 27 games (dating to 2014\u201315 season).<ref>{{cite news|title=Spurs 18-0 at home after 101-95 win over Timberwolves|url=http://www.nba.com/games/20151228/MINSAS/gameinfo.html|accessdate=December 29, 2015|work=NBA.com|date=December 28, 2015}}</ref> Two days later, in a win over the [[Phoenix Suns]], he became the first player in Spurs franchise history to record 12 rebounds in 15 minutes or less.<ref>{{cite news|title=Aldridge's double-double helps Spurs rout Suns 112-79|url=http://www.nba.com/games/20151230/PHXSAS/gameinfo.html|accessdate=December 31, 2015|work=NBA.com|date=December 30, 2015}}</ref> On January 21, 2016, he recorded 17 points and a career-high 13 rebounds in a 117\u201389 win over the [[Phoenix Suns]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nba.com/games/20160121/SASPHX/gameinfo.html|title=Spurs cruise to 12th straight win, 117-89 win over Suns|work=NBA.com|date=January 21, 2016|accessdate=January 22, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160121181145/http://www.nba.com/games/20160121/SASPHX/gameinfo.html|archive-date=January 21, 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> On March 20, he was reassigned to the Austin Spurs,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nba.com/spurs/spurs-assign-boban-marjanovic-jonathon-simmons-austin-spurs|title=SPURS ASSIGN BOBAN MARJANOVIC & JONATHON SIMMONS TO AUSTIN SPURS|date=March 20, 2016|work=NBA.com|accessdate=March 20, 2016}}</ref> earning a recall two days later.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nba.com/spurs/spurs-recall-boban-marjanovic-jonathon-simmons-austin-spurs|title=SPURS RECALL BOBAN MARJANOVIC & JONATHON SIMMONS FROM AUSTIN SPURS|date=March 22, 2016|work=NBA.com|accessdate=March 22, 2016}}</ref> On March 23, he scored a then career-high 19 points in a 112\u201388 win over the [[Miami Heat]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nba.com/games/20160323/MIASAS/gameinfo.html|title=Leonard matches career high with 32, Spurs beat Heat 112-88|date=March 23, 2016|work=NBA.com|accessdate=March 24, 2016}}</ref> On April 13, in the team's regular season finale, Marjanovi\u0107 recorded a career-high 22 points and 12 rebounds in a 96\u201391 win over the [[Dallas Mavericks]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nba.com/games/20160413/SASDAL/gameinfo.html|title=Spurs sit 4 starters, top Mavs; game ultimately meaningless|date=April 13, 2016|work=NBA.com|accessdate=April 13, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160417205518/http://www.nba.com/games/20160413/SASDAL/gameinfo.html|archive-date=April 17, 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n===Detroit Pistons (2016\u20132018)===\nAfter the 2015\u201316 season, Marjanovi\u0107 became a [[NBA salary cap#Restricted free agent|restricted free agent]]. On July 7, 2016, he received a three-year, $21 million offer sheet from the [[Detroit Pistons]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Boban Marjanovic signs three-year offer sheet with Pistons|url=http://espn.go.com/nba/story/_/id/16857694/boban-marjanovic-agrees-contract-detroit-pistons-san-antonio-spurs-chance-match|work=ESPN.com|date=July 7, 2016|accessdate=July 12, 2016}}</ref> The Spurs declined to match the offer<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://twitter.com/David_Mayo/status/752277319805382657 |title=Source confirms Spurs have opted not to match... |last=Mayo |first=David |date=July 10, 2016 |website=Twitter |access-date=July 10, 2016}}</ref> and he signed with the Pistons on July 12.<ref>{{cite web|title=Detroit Pistons Sign Free Agent Boban Marjanovic|url=http://www.nba.com/pistons/news/detroit-pistons-sign-free-agent-boban-marjanovic|work=NBA.com|date=July 12, 2016|accessdate=July 12, 2016}}</ref> On January 5, 2017, Marjanovi\u0107 recorded 15 points and a career-high 19 rebounds in a 115\u2013114 win over the [[Charlotte Hornets]]. He had played only 76 minutes all season prior to the game against the Hornets but, with [[Andre Drummond]] in foul trouble and [[Aron Baynes]] out injured, coach [[Stan Van Gundy]] had to give Marjanovi\u0107 extended minutes.<ref>{{cite web|title=Pistons hold off Hornets when Belinelli's shot is too late|url=http://www.espn.com.au/nba/recap?gameId=400899959|work=ESPN.com|date=January 5, 2017|accessdate=January 6, 2017}}</ref> On April 7, 2017, he led the Pistons with a career-high 27 points and 12 rebounds off the bench in a 114\u2013109 win over the [[Houston Rockets]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/nba/recap?gameId=400900560|title=Johnson hits late 3-pointer, Pistons beat Rockets 114-109|work=ESPN.com|date=April 7, 2017|accessdate=April 8, 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Los Angeles Clippers (2018\u20132019)===\nOn January 29, 2018, Marjanovi\u0107, along with [[Tobias Harris]], [[Avery Bradley]], a future protected first-round draft pick and a future second round draft pick, was traded to the [[Los Angeles Clippers]] in exchange for [[Blake Griffin]], [[Willie Reed]] and [[Brice Johnson]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nba.com/clippers/press-release-clippers-acquire-harris-bradley-marjanovic|title=Press Release: L.A. Clippers Acquire Harris, Bradley, Marjanovi\u0107, First & Second-Round Picks|work=NBA.com|date=January 29, 2018|accessdate=January 30, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nba.com/article/2018/01/30/detroit-pistons-acquire-griffin-harris-bradley-marjanovic-release|title=Detroit Pistons acquire Blake Griffin, Willie Reed, Brice Johnson from LA Clippers|work=NBA.com|date=January 30, 2018|accessdate=January 30, 2018}}</ref> On February 27, 2018, he scored a season-high 18 points in a 122\u2013120 win over the Denver Nuggets.\n\n===Philadelphia 76ers (2019)===\nOn February 6, 2019, Marjanovi\u0107 alongside his teammate [[Tobias Harris]] was traded to the [[Philadelphia 76ers]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nba.com/sixers/news/harris-marjanovic-and-scott-acquired-la-clippers|title=Harris, Marjanovi\u0107, and Scott Acquired From LA Clippers|work=NBA.com|date=February 6, 2019|accessdate=February 6, 2019}}</ref> In 22 appearances for the 76ers in the [[2018\u201319 Philadelphia 76ers season|regular season]], Marjanovi\u0107 averaged 8.2 points and 5.1 rebounds in 13.9 minutes per game. He later helped the 76ers get past the [[Brooklyn Nets]] in First Round of [[2019 NBA playoffs]],<ref>{{cite news |last1=Levick |first1=Noah |title=Boban Marjanovic's size is impossible to ignore, but he's more than a novelty |url=https://www.nbcsports.com/philadelphia/76ers/boban-marjanovic-size-impossible-ignore-more-than-novelty-nba-playoffs |accessdate=18 May 2019 |work=nbcsports.com/ |date=19 April 2019}}</ref> but the 76ers were eventually eliminated by [[Toronto Raptors]] in Conference Semifinals.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Gozlan |first1=Yossi |title=An early preview of the 2019-20 offseason for the Philadelphia |url=https://sixerswire.usatoday.com/2019/05/16/an-early-preview-of-the-2019-20-offseason-for-the-philadelphia-sixers/ |accessdate=18 May 2019 |work=usatoday.com |date=16 May 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Dallas Mavericks (2019\u2013present)===\nOn July 23, 2019, he signed with the [[Dallas Mavericks]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mavs.com/mavs-sign-philadelphia-76ers-free-agent-center-boban-marjanovic/|title=Mavs sign Philadelphia 76ers free agent center Boban Marjanovic|website=NBA.com|date=July 23, 2019|accessdate=July 23, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn March 11, 2020, Marjanovic scored a career-high 31 points, along with 17 rebounds, in a 113-97 win over the [[Denver Nuggets]], in what was the final game before the [[Suspension of the 2019\u201320 NBA season|season was suspended]] due to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|coronavirus pandemic]].<ref> https://www.espn.com/nba/game?gameId=401161615</ref><ref name=\"nba-suspension-of-season\">{{cite press release|title=NBA to suspend season following tonight\u2019s games|publisher=National Basketball Association|date=March 11, 2020|url=https://pr.nba.com/nba-to-suspend-season-following-tonights-games/|accessdate=March 12, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==National team career==\n{{see also|2017 Serbia men's EuroBasket team}}\nAs a junior national team player with Serbia, Marjanovi\u0107 won gold medals at the [[2007 FIBA Under-19 World Championship]] and the [[2008 FIBA Europe Under-20 Championship]]. He was named on the candidates list before both the [[EuroBasket 2009]] and the [[2010 FIBA World Championship]], but did not get in the final 12-man squads. His senior debut with the [[Serbian national basketball team]] at a major tournament came at [[EuroBasket 2011]] in [[Lithuania]], where Serbia finished in 8th place.\n\nIn August 2015, the San Antonio Spurs prohibited him from playing for the Serbian national team at [[EuroBasket 2015]] due to risk of injury after signs of pain in his left foot, although the [[Serbian Basketball Federation|Serbian Basketball Federation (KSS)]] stated that no bone fractures were found.<ref>{{cite news|title=Marjanovic Return To National Team Postponed|url=http://www.eurobasket2015.org/en/compID_qMRZdYCZI6EoANOrUf9le2.season_2015.roundID_9322.coid_1w8pON5UIsshfP8zWVLZX3.articleMode_on.html|accessdate=24 August 2015|work=Eurobasket2015.org|date=4 August 2015}}</ref>\n\nMarjanovi\u0107 represented Serbia at [[EuroBasket 2017]]. They won the silver medal, losing the final to [[Slovenia national basketball team|Slovenia]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Slovenia overcome injuries to claim historic title in Dragic's swansong|url=http://www.fiba.basketball/eurobasket/2017/news/slovenia-overcome-injuries-to-claim-historic-title|accessdate=17 September 2017|work=FIBA.basketball|date=17 September 2017|language=en}}</ref> Over 9 tournament games, he averaged 12.4 points, 4.8 rebounds and 1.4 assists per game on 56.2% shooting from the field.\n\nAt the [[2019 FIBA Basketball World Cup]], the national team of Serbia was dubbed as favorite to win the trophy,<ref>{{cite news |last1=Curkovic |first1=Igor |title=FIBA Basketball World Cup Power Rankings, Volume 3 |url=http://www.fiba.basketball/basketballworldcup/2019/news/fiba-basketball-world-cup-power-rankings-volume-3 |accessdate=14 September 2019 |work=fiba.basketball |date=28 August 2019}}</ref> but was eventually upset in the [[2019 FIBA Basketball World Cup final round|quarterfinals]] by [[Argentina national basketball team|Argentina]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Argentina upsets Olympic silver medalist Serbia in FIBA World Cup quarterfinals |url=https://olympics.nbcsports.com/2019/09/10/argentina-serbia-fiba-world-cup/ |accessdate=14 September 2019 |work=nbcsports.com |date=10 September 2019}}</ref> With wins over the [[United States men's national basketball team|United States]] and [[Czech Republic national basketball team|Czech Republic]], it finished in fifth place.<ref>{{cite news |title=Serbia defeats USA in FIBA World Cup consolation round play |url=https://www.nba.com/article/2019/09/12/fiba-world-cup-usa-serbia-game-recap |accessdate=14 September 2019 |work=nba.com |date=12 September 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=T. |first1=P. |title=Bogdanovi\u0107 ponovo briljirao \u2013 Srbiji peto mesto u Kini |url=https://www.b92.net/sport/kina2019/vesti.php?nav_id=1591176 |accessdate=14 September 2019 |date=14 September 2019 |language=Serbian}}</ref> Marjanovi\u0107 averaged 6.8 points and 2.5 rebounds over 8 games.\n\n==Career statistics==\n{{Euroleague player statistics legend}}\n\n===NBA===\n\n====Regular season====\n{{NBA player statistics start}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{nbay|2015}}\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[2015\u201316 San Antonio Spurs season|San Antonio]]\n| '''54''' || 4 || 9.4 || .603 || {{sort|-|\u2014}} || .763 || 3.6 || .4 || .2 || .4 || 5.5\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{nbay|2016}}\